      • createSummaryDefect

        IWorkItem createSummaryDefect(IWorkItem defectTemplate)
        Creates a summary defect based on the given template and stores it to KEY_SUMMARY_DEFECT field of this Test Run if it does not exist yet, otherwise just returns the existing summary defect. It is not needed to call IPObject.save() on this Test Run or IPObject.save() on the returned object.
        Parameters:
        defectTemplate - when null, then work item configured by TestsConfiguration.getDefectTemplate() for the project is used.
        Returns:
        the created defect Work Item

      • updateSummaryDefect

        IWorkItem updateSummaryDefect(java.lang.String source,
                              int totalFailures,
                              int totalErrors,
                              int totalTests,
                              IWorkItem defectTemplate)
        Updates description of the summary defect by appending a standard text about the counts of tests with the different results. Creates a new summary defect using the createSummaryDefect(IWorkItem) method if it does not exist yet. It is not needed to call IPObject.save() on the returned object.
        Parameters:
        source - string description of the automated test import source, for example name of the input file
        totalFailures - count of failed test
        totalErrors - count of tests with error
        totalTests - total count of tests
        defectTemplate - passed to method createSummaryDefect(IWorkItem) when it is called

        Creates the (temporary) attachment object, which can be manipulated by the client. However, the attachment is not persisted until it's explicitly saved.
